es. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth was born in 1257, in Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William de Saye IV in 1277, in Elsenham, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 3 daughters. She died about 1310, in Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1257–about 1310":"1257–umbes 1310","1253–1292":"1253–1292","1280–1320":"1280–1320","1281–1322":"1281–1322","1283–1305":"1283–1305","1285–Female":"1285–Surnud","1257–1310":"1257–1310","Abt. 1280":"umbes 1280","1 April 1281":"1. aprill 1281","1253":"1253","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1292":"1292","1281":"1281","1280":"1280","1305":"1305","1257":"1257","1322":"1322","1277":"1277","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"umbes 1310","Elsenham, Essex, England":"Elsenham, Essex, England","Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Great Linton, Cambridgeshire, England.":"Cambridgeshire, England","Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","West Malling, Kent, England":"West Malling, Kent, England","Berling, Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1257–about 1310":"1257–noin 1310","1253–1292":"1253–1292","1280–1320":"1280–1320","1281–1322":"1281–1322","1283–1305":"1283–1305","1285–Female":"1285–Kuollut","1257–1310":"1257–1310","Abt. 1280":"noin 1280","1 April 1281":"1. huhtikuuta 1281","1253":"1253","1285":"1285","1283":"1283","1292":"1292","1281":"1281","1280":"1280","1305":"1305","1257":"1257","1322":"1322","1277":"1277","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"noin 1310","Elsenham, Essex, England":"Elsenh